<Author>MickyPa
<Content>B Hotel was the B-est!! We spent two nights at the B Hotel and we absolutely enjoyed our stay. On our arrival we were greeted by a very nice girl, who gave us all the informations we needed on how to get around, even handing us a very useful map of the city. The Hotel is situated right next to Plaza Espana and a 30 minutes walk to Las Ramblas and Placa Catalonya. We don't usually use public transportation but the Hotel is very close to a metro station which it would take you everywhere you need to go. In Placa Espana you will be able to get a bus to and from the airport for only 1.60 euro, which is very convenient. We do not reccomend taking a taxi from the airport, they all charge a flat rate of 35 euro, and the Hotel is only 20 minutes away, so the price seemed very high.We were given a room facing the street, and even though the traffic can be pretty busy, we weren't bother too much by the noise coming from the outside. The room had a beautiful modern feeling, with a very nice bathroom, a flat screen TV and a little fridge filled up with all kind of drinks.Breakfast wasn't included in our room rate so we decided to take advantage of the buffet only on the last morning before our departure. The price was a bit high, 13 euro per person, but it was well worth it. The buffet had all kind of food like cereal, cheeses, salami, eggs, fresh fruit salad, yogurt and sweets. Plus coffee and tea to order. There is enough food to fill you up for good part of the day.We would recommend this to anyone. 
