<Author>Martin68
<Content>Simply superb Location is a little out of the centre but I didn't find it a problem. The hotel is five minutes walk from the Placa Espanya metro stop and you can get into the centre very quickly or it's a 20 min walk to Placa Catlunya.Had a 6th floor room facing Grand Via. It is a very busy road and there was traffic noise but this is a city hotel so it's fair to expect it and it didn't bother me. If you're a light sleeper, there are some rooms on the inside of the hotel that you might want to ask for. The room is a good size with large desk, comfortable chair and sofa. There is a full length door and tiny balcony that you can step out on for a bit of fresh air. Bathroom is good with a decent sized bath and seriously powerful shower which amazingly doesn't go all over the floor like most do.The mood lighting in the room (but not the bathroom) is really excellent and it's all controlled by buttons at the door and bed which cycle through various settings. Venetian blinds to the bathroom are fun (the controls are below the bathroom mirror in case you're wondering!). Wi-fi is free, fast and reliable (and as a bonus works on the roof terrace which is stunning!).The buffet breakfast was absolutely excellent with a wide selection and staff that kept the food topped up, cleared/reset tables and actually seemed to take pride in their job. In many hotels the buffet breakfast seems to be an excuse for the staff to hide away as much as possible so full marks to B-Hotel. I used room service once and it was good. The menu is pretty basic but fresh, well cooked and reasonably priced compared to many hotels.The staff were friendly, attentive, efficient and helpful throughout.The niggles are few and far between. The safe is slightly too small for a 15 laptop and the designer should be shot for the lack of decent lighting anywhere near a mirror!All in all, this is a really fabulous hotel for travellers on a midrange budget who appreciate contemporary design. Note you can get extra discount by booking more than 30 days in advance on the hotel's own website. I rate B-Hotel very highly indeed for a 3 star and would definitely stay there again. 
