-handed鈥?so you need to hold the ticket in your left hand and pass to the right of the barrier. I saw many tourists trying to walk through the barrier to the left of the ticket-checker, and being puzzled that they could not advance 鈥?we did this ourselves, at first!Sights near the hotel include the Montjuic area, with a cable car up to the Castle 鈥?excellent views on clear days. The 鈥榤agic fountain鈥?is very near, as is the National Palace 鈥?a very large art gallery. In town, queues for Gaudi鈥檚 Sagrada Familia (cathedral) and 鈥楲a Pedrera鈥?(town house) were very long 鈥?go early if you want to get inside these. It is easier to get in to the beautiful and highly original Casa Batllo, a short way down the road from La Pedrera. Another spectacular building is the Palau de la M煤sica Catalana (concert hall) 鈥?well worth a visit, with drinks and tapas available in the foyer 鈥?try to catch a concert, if you want to see the upstairs areas. We didn鈥檛 come close to seeing everything worth visiting in 3 days 鈥?so we鈥檒l be going back! 
