<Content>A Fun Change We chose the B-Hotel on the basis of the reviews in TripAdvisor - well done fellow travellers!The Hotel is modern and clean - and whilst we had trouble finding the front door (sliding wooden panel amongst all the glass) and struggled a bit with the lights in the room (too many possible combinations) - we would definately stay again.The location was great - and even being right by a building site (They are turning the old bullring into a shopping /entertainment centre) and the Placa Espanya it wasn't noisy. We had a great corner room lots of space and a huge bed. The shower got water everywhere - but once I remembered it wouldn't be me mopping it up it was cool!The rooftop pool / relax area was fantastic for a sunset beer and snackTea and Coffee in the room and the bar opening after 11pm would have given it an excellent score.We didn't do breakfast in the hotel (12 Euros each was a bit steep) but went along the Grand Via towards the centre - two blocks down for a great coffee, juice and fresh croissant. The food / beer / service at the Suarna Restaurant - cross over the Grand Via and head for the blue lights - was great too and full of locals which is always a good sign.We bought the Barcelona Bus Tour (not Bus Turistic) and the Barcelona Card via Expedia at the same tome as paying for the hotel - good move. The vouchers can be redeemed in the airport info desk and a new bus route (no 46) goes from terminal B of the airport to the Placa Espanya and is included in the Barcelona Card which also gives you loads of money off offers and free stuff.The Barcelona Bus goes from Placa Espanya and the voucher can be redeemed on board - there are less buses than the Bus Turistic - but the route is simpler and has less people on board as a result! 
