ould be useful if there were coffee making facilities in the room as with all UK and US hotels. The pool on the roof was very handy for a little rest after a busy day and was very quiet. There is a Metro station within a couple of minutes walk which connects you with the rest of the city (buy a ticket to cover you for the number of days you are there). There really aren鈥檛 many places to eat or drink in the immediate vicinity, so this is very useful. If you are heading for Las Ramblas or nearby in the evening, the green line takes you directly there and the trains run until midnight (or 2am on Fridays and Saturdays). They are also very safe even at such late hours. 
