<Content>Great hotel, but trip was marred by some issues We booked an 8-day stay at the B-Hotel based on Trip Advisor reviews. Whilst we were very impressed by the sleekness of the hotel, there were some issues which really marred our stay. I'll list my comments as positives and negatives to (hopefully!) provide a balanced review:Positives- Very sleek hotel with ultra modern decor- Sophisticated lighting system in room with different sequences (e.g. the nighttime toilet sequence turned on a dim light beneath the bedside table and lit a dim walkway to the bathroom)- Amazing rooftop swimming pool- Perfectly situated next to Place d'Espanya (on two good tube lines which provided quick - 5 minute - journeys to the centre). You could walk to the Ramblas in around 20 minutes. Also, Espanya is a key rail station so excellent for day trips out of the city (we went to Montserrat and it was very convenient).- Quick and efficient check-in and out- Free internet access- Hotel bar with reasonably priced drinks- Room service (which we didn't try, but had well-priced options)- Reasonably priced.Negatives- One of the reasons I booked this hotel was for the gym. I am an athlete and needed to train at least three times whilst visiting (I was due to run in a race a few days after our return to England). Despite all literature saying a gym existed (including Expedia), there was no gym at the hotel (only a pool). Reception were not helpful in finding us other options, and were not apologetic. I had to pay for fitness facilities elsewhere (the hotel refused to pay, despite their own false advertising!). We are going to receive a refund for the gym fees and compensation from our tour operator (thank you Expedia!), but this left a sour taste in our mouths. Check before you leave if you do require a gym as I believe they are planning to put one in at some point.- Although our room maid changed the bedclothes and towels daily, the sink and bathroom floor were not cleaned all week, and we also don't think the room was hoovered.- The hotel was poorly soundproofed. On three occasions, other guests held all night parties and we could hear *every* sound. However, the double glazing IS good if you're staying on the road side.- We were put on a smoking floor despite asking for the contrary.- Although the rooms were sleek, there was some bad finishing. We had to wedge our sink open with a comb, the room door had to be rammed open and the maid broke our bath plug halfway through the week (this wasn't replaced).- Minor point: There is only one english-speaking TV channel (BBC World).- Minor point: The bar shuts at 11pm (bear in mind most people in Barcelona don't eat before 10pm, so it would have been nice to have had a drink on our return).- Very minor point: The internet was only available until 10.45pm.Overall, the B-Hotel IS good value for money and I would recommend it for the price you pay. However, don't be surprised if you encounter some issues during your stay - although hopefully they'll be minor! 
