<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>The Best! We stayed at this hotel as part of a 1 month tour of Europe and can say without doubt it was our favourite! Modern, stylish and lots of gadgets! The staff were very helpful, the room was heavenly - very tastefully decorated and a good location. We walked into town in about 20 minutes, or there is a metro (Plaza Espanya) right outside. I think the 3 star rating is unfair but reflects the fact that it doesn't have its own resturant, but does serve food, however there are a few cafes and resturants nearby as well as town. There is a supermarket (OpenCor) 2 minutes walk for essential snacks. There is internet access on the first floor for those without a laptop (two computers, but only one was working). The rooftop pool is great with excellent views. I would recommend this and stay again! 
